name: MonetaryAmount
label: monetary amount
definition: measure that is an amount of money specified in monetary units

name: CurrencyIdentifier
label: currency identifier
definition: sequence of characters representing some currency
explanatoryNote: The first (left-most) two characters of the ISO 4217 3-letter currency identifier relate to the currency authority that issues the currency, and is, in most cases the ISO 3166-1 alpha 2 code for the geopolitical entity whose central bank is the issuer. The third (right-most) character of the identifier (alphabetic code) is an indicator derived from the name of the major currency unit or fund. If the currency is not associated with a single geographical entity as described in ISO 3166-1, typically a specially allocated identifier (alpha-2 code) is used to describe the currency authority. This code has been allocated by the Maintenance Agency from within the user-assigned range of codes XA to XZ specified in 8.1.3 of ISO 3166-1:2013. The character following X will be a mnemonic, where possible, derived from the name of the geographical area concerned.

name: MonetaryPrice
label: monetary price
definition: price that that is expressed as a monetary amount
explanatoryNote: As the consideration given in exchange for transfer of ownership, price forms the essential basis of commercial transactions. It may be fixed by a contract, left to be determined by an agreed upon formula at a future date, or discovered or negotiated during the course of dealings between the parties involved. In commerce, price is determined by what (1) a buyer is willing to pay, (2) a seller is willing to accept, and (3) the competition is allowing to be charged.

name: Price
definition: amount of money, goods, or services requested, expected, required, or given in exchange for something else
label: price

name: FundsIdentifier
label: funds identifier
definition: sequence of characters that can be used to uniquely identify funds

name: PreciousMetalIdentifier
definition: sequence of characters uniquely identifying the precious metal in some context
label: precious metal identifier

name: InterestRate
label: interest rate
definition: amount charged, expressed as a percentage of principal, in exchange for the use of assets
explanatoryNote: Interest rates are typically noted on an annual basis, known as the annual percentage rate (APR). The assets borrowed could include cash, consumer goods, and large assets such as a vehicle or building. The rate is derived by dividing the amount of interest by the amount of principal borrowed. Interest rates are quoted on bills, notes, bonds, credit cards, and many kinds of consumer and business loans.

name: PercentageMonetaryAmount
definition: measure of some amount of money expressed as a percentage of some other amount, some notional amount or some concrete money amount
label: percentage monetary amount

name: AmountOfMoney
label: amount of money
definition: amount of readily available cash in banknotes and coins

name: UnitOfAccountIdentifier
label: unit of account identifier
definition: sequence of characters that can be used to uniquely identify a nominal monetary unit

name: Currency
definition: medium of exchange value, defined by reference to the geographical location of the monetary authorities responsible for it
label: currency

name: Funds
label: funds
definition: artificial currency used as calculation basis for another currency(s) and accounting purposes

name: CalculatedPrice
definition: monetary price determined by a formula
label: calculated price

name: UnitPrice
label: unit price
definition: monetary price expressed in relation to a well-known measurable unit by which the goods or services are allocated

name: UnitOfAccount
label: unit of account
definition: nominal monetary unit of measure used to represent the real value (or cost) of any economic item; i.e. goods, services, assets, liabilities, income, expenses

name: ExchangeRate
definition: rate at which one currency can be exchanged for another
label: exchange rate

name: PreciousMetal
definition: metal that is considered to be rare and/or have a high economic value
label: precious metal

name: CurrencyBasket
definition: selected group of currencies, in which the weighted average is used as a measure of the value or the amount of an obligation
label: currency basket

name: hasFundsType
label: has funds type
definition: indicates the type of funds, such as next day for US funds

name: hasAmount
label: has amount
definition: total number or quantity

name: hasMinorUnit
definition: relates a code for the minor unit of currency to the currency or fund
label: has minor unit

name: hasNumericCode
label: has numeric code
definition: relates a numeric code to something, such as a currency or fund

name: hasDealtCurrency
definition: specifies a unit of currency representing the exchanged (target) currency in an exchange rate; R units of this currency represent one unit of the base currency
label: has dealt currency

name: hasMonetaryAmount
definition: specifies a value for something in terms of an amount of money and the currency in which it is denoted
label: has monetary amount

name: hasNotionalAmount
definition: has a generally unchangeable value used for certain calculations, expressed as some monetary amount
label: has notional amount
explanatoryNote: For certain kinds of derivative instruments, including but not limited to swaps, the notional amount indicates face amount of a swap upon which the payment streams for that swap are based. While this is typically constant throughout the lifetime of a contract, it can be accreting, amortizing, or custom, such as in the case of a notional step schedule.

name: hasBaseCurrency
label: has base currency
definition: specifies a unit of currency representing R units of the dealt currency, where R is the exchange rate value, in an exchange rate

name: hasPrice
label: has price
definition: indicates the value of something expressed as an amount of money or goods

name: hasRateValue
definition: has a value for a rate expressed as a number (may be a percentage or raw number)
label: has rate value

name: isPriceFor
label: is price for
definition: links a price to something it provides a value for

name: hasCurrency
definition: specifies the medium of exchange value in which something, such as a monetary amount is denominated
label: has currency
